53
00:01:57,410 --> 00:02:00,400
And there's a few phrases we
can use for this in English.

54
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:03,990
Sometimes for me, a certain
month will go by really quickly.

55
00:02:03,990 --> 00:02:07,060
And I would use the
phrase, that went by fast,

56
00:02:07,060 --> 00:02:08,150
and I can be specific.

57
00:02:08,150 --> 00:02:11,340
I could say, wow, that month went by fast.

58
00:02:11,340 --> 00:02:13,540
And we have a few more phrases as well.

59
00:02:13,540 --> 00:02:16,250
Sometimes we ask this question, we'll say,

60
00:02:16,250 --> 00:02:18,230
where did the time go?

61
00:02:18,230 --> 00:02:20,750
When you say, where did
the time go in English,

62
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:23,490
you're expressing that
something in the past

63
00:02:23,490 --> 00:02:25,490
just happened really, really quickly.

64
00:02:25,490 --> 00:02:27,670
I could say, wow, it's already October.

65
00:02:27,670 --> 00:02:29,870
Where did the time go?

66
00:02:29,870 --> 00:02:31,990
Sometimes we use this phrase as well.

67
00:02:31,990 --> 00:02:35,010
We'll say, it seems like just yesterday.

68
00:02:35,010 --> 00:02:37,250
And we use this phrase to introduce

69
00:02:38,430 --> 00:02:40,130
an idea to the conversation.

70
00:02:40,130 --> 00:02:42,290
The best one I can think of is this.

71
00:02:42,290 --> 00:02:43,540
Because I have children,

72
00:02:43,540 --> 00:02:46,160
I could say it seems like just yesterday,

73
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:47,440
they were really little.

74
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:49,230
They've all grown up quite a bit by now.

75
00:02:49,230 --> 00:02:52,710
So sometimes when we talk
about how time goes quickly,

76
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:55,760
we'll use the phrase, it
seems like just yesterday.

77
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:58,270
And there's a phrase that
you're probably familiar with,

78
00:02:58,270 --> 00:02:59,460
time flies.

79
00:02:59,460 --> 00:03:02,500
Sometimes we add time flies
when you're having fun,

80
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:05,990
but sometimes we'll just say,
whoa, time flies, doesn't it?

81
00:03:05,990 --> 00:03:08,860
When you talk about a month
that went by quickly, or a year,

82
00:03:08,860 --> 00:03:11,580
sometimes a whole year goes
by, and you're like wow,

83
00:03:11,580 --> 00:03:13,970
it's already 2021.

84
00:03:13,970 --> 00:03:15,330
Wow, time flies.

85
00:03:15,330 --> 00:03:17,780
Actually 2021's almost over, isn't it?

86
00:03:17,780 --> 00:03:19,990
Wow, time flies.

87
00:03:19,990 --> 00:03:22,730
