to pick up your friend.

102
00:03:57,300 --> 00:04:01,030
And if you found out their
flight was delayed by four hours,

103
00:04:01,030 --> 00:04:03,900
you would then say, oh,
I have time to kill.

104
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:05,850
You have an amount of time

105
00:04:05,850 --> 00:04:07,700
where you really can't do anything else.

106
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:09,070
You need to wait for them.

107
00:04:09,070 --> 00:04:11,160
So in that case, we would
use that English phrase.

108
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:13,660
We would say, you have time to kill.

109
00:04:13,660 --> 00:04:15,180
Of course, there's also times

110
00:04:15,180 --> 00:04:16,829
when you don't have enough time,

111
00:04:16,829 --> 00:04:20,079
where you are in a hurry,
or you are in a rush.

112
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:21,449
And then we would probably say

113
00:04:21,450 --> 00:04:23,550
that you are pressed for time.

114
00:04:23,550 --> 00:04:26,810
Sometimes in the morning when
I'm getting ready for work,

115
00:04:26,810 --> 00:04:28,180
I'm running a little bit late,

116
00:04:28,180 --> 00:04:29,550
and then I'm pressed for time.

117
00:04:29,550 --> 00:04:32,770
It simply means that I'm
in a rush, I'm in a hurry.

118
00:04:32,770 --> 00:04:35,340
I'm going to be late for
work if I don't get moving.

119
00:04:35,340 --> 00:04:37,310
So when you're pressed for time,

120
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:39,670
it means you're probably going
to be late for something.

121
00:04:39,670 --> 00:04:42,340
And then we also use kind of the negative

122
00:04:42,340 --> 00:04:43,870
of a phrase I taught you earlier.

123
00:04:43,870 --> 00:04:46,960
We might say that you don't
have all the time in the world.

124
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:49,360
This is something that I
might say to my children.

125
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:50,860
If I'm ready to go and they're not,

126
00:04:50,860 --> 00:04:52,740
I might say, let's get going.

127
00:04:52,740 --> 00:04:55,560
I don't have all the time in the world.

128
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:58,050
So sometimes you're late,
sometimes you're in a hurry,

129
00:04:58,050 --> 00:04:59,870
and you can use one of those two phrases.

130
00:04:59,870 --> 00:05:01,590
You could say I'm pressed for time,

131
00:05:01,590 --> 00:05:03,550
or hey, hurry up, everybody.

132
00:05:03,550 --> 00:05:06,610
I don't have all the time in the world.

133
