In that situation,

137
00:05:14,210 --> 00:05:17,390
you would use the English
phrase in the blink of an eye.

138
00:05:17,390 --> 00:05:19,020
You could say I was driving along,

139
00:05:19,020 --> 00:05:20,230
and then in the blink of an eye,

140
00:05:20,230 --> 00:05:22,780
someone pulled out in front
of me, and I hit them.

141
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:23,930
That wouldn't be very nice,

142
00:05:23,930 --> 00:05:26,070
but that is the English
phrase you would use.

143
00:05:26,070 --> 00:05:28,860
You would say it happened
in the blink of an eye.

144
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:31,900
Sometimes when I go to my
classroom, I forget something,

145
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:35,520
and I have to go back to my
teacher work area to get it.

146
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,280
In that situation, I
would say to students,

147
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:38,900
I'll be back in a flash.

148
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:40,840
The English phrase in a flash

149
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:43,730
